ğŸ§˜â€â™‚ï¸ PrismX Zen Mode â€“ README

Zen Mode is a minimal-distraction writing interface designed for focused task triage, journaling, or ideation within PrismX. It enables a keyboard-first scratchpad experience with autosave, centered layout, typewriter scrolling, and fade-in UI elements.

ğŸ“Œ Features

Feature	Description
Ctrl + Z	Toggle Zen Mode on/off
Ctrl + Alt + N	Instantly open the autosaving scratchpad in Zen Mode
Hidden UI	All sidebars, toolbars, and clutter are hidden
Centered scratchpad	Text is vertically and horizontally centered for typewriter-style focus
Fade-in title bar	Displays minimal status line after a short delay
Autosave (default: 10s)	Scratchpad changes are saved automatically
Manual Save (Ctrl + S)	Instantly saves scratchpad content
Typewriter scrolling	Cursor stays centered while typing
Robust error handling	Fallbacks for missing or corrupt scratchpad files
Extreme logging (toggleable)	All actions are logged to logs/zen_debug.log
ğŸ”§ Configuration

Located in ~/.config/prismx/config.toml (optional â€“ defaults apply if absent):

[zen_mode]
title_fade_delay_secs = 2
autosave_interval_secs = 10
scratchpad_path = "~/.config/prismx/zen_scratchpad.md"
ğŸ’¡ Shortcuts Reference (Zen Mode)

Keybinding	Description
Ctrl + Z	Toggle Zen Mode
Ctrl + Alt + N	Open scratchpad (activates Zen Mode)
Ctrl + S	Manual save of current content
Ctrl + D	Toggle debug logging (runtime only)
Esc	Exit Zen Mode
